<div id="banner">
	<h1>Ideal PDA</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Everyone&#8217;s getting a Hiptop/Sidekick, but it doesn&#8217;t seem to have all the things I need. I will buy a WearableGizmo (i.e. something that fits in my pocket) if it has:</p>

<ul>
<li>a reasonably-large screen</li>
<li>a usable interface</li>
<li>a cell-phone Internet connection</li>
<li>Web client</li>
<li>IMAP mail client</li>
<li>SSH client</li>
</ul>

<p>Ideally, it will also have:</p>

<ul>
<li>a cell phone</li>
<li>IRC client</li>
<li>high-quality camera</li>
<li>802.11 support</li>
<li>support for third-party apps</li>
<li>support for third-party apps in Python</li>
</ul>

<p>Does such a thing exist? I doubt it&#8230; maybe I should just stay with my laptop.</p>

<p class="posted">posted December 31, 2002 03:43 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000783" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
